The article discusses the importance of advancing inclusion and belonging for people of all races, national origins, and ethnicities in order to ensure the safety and security of the American people. It highlights how the COVID-19 pandemic has led to increased xenophobic rhetoric and discrimination against Asian American and Pacific Islander (AAPI) individuals, putting them at risk. The article acknowledges that the Federal Government has played a role in perpetuating this xenophobia through references to the geographic origin of the pandemic. It emphasizes the need to combat racism, xenophobia, and intolerance against AAPI communities and ensure that they are treated with dignity and equity. The article also outlines specific actions that the Federal Government should take, such as issuing guidance on cultural competency and language access, ensuring official actions and statements do not contribute to discrimination, and supporting efforts to prevent hate crimes and collect data on hate incidents. The memorandum concludes with provisions for implementation and publication.